-- Renewables’ Role in Power Plant Closures Overstated, SocGen Says
-- B y   R a c h e l   M o r i s o n
-- 2012-11-22T10:20:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-22/renewables-role-in-power-plant-closures-overstated-socgen-says.html
The role of renewables in
influencing European utilities when deciding to build or close
power stations may be overstated, according to  Societe Generale
SA. (GLE)   “The contribution to utility profits from the balancing
market is becoming more important,” Alberto Ponti, managing
director and head of European utilities at the French bank, told
delegates at a conference in Amsterdam.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Morison in London at 
 rmorison@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
